      "intro": "If your parent is struggling with high energy bills, Maryland's Weatherization Assistance Program provides free home improvements that reduce heating and cooling costs by an average of 30-35%. The program installs insulation, fixes air leaks, tunes up furnaces, and makes other energy efficiency upgrades at no cost to qualifying homeowners and renters.\n\nYour parent may qualify if their household income is below $48,085 for a single person or $62,880 for a couple (2026 limits). The program automatically accepts families already receiving SNAP, TANF, SSI, or certain utility assistance programs. Priority goes to households with seniors age 60+, people with disabilities, or families with young children.\n\nBecause this is a federal program delivered through local agencies, your parent will work with energy specialists in their area who assess the home and complete all improvements using certified contractors. There's no dollar limit per home — the upgrades are based on what the energy assessment shows will help most.",
